#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Musāvādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 1"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "1. Musāvādasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on lying"

#. </h1></div><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.164"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1"></a><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa2"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs0.6"
msgid "Ime kho panāyasmanto dvenavuti pācittiyā dhammā uddesaṃ āgacchanti."
msgstr ""
"Venerables, these ninety-two rules entailing confession come up for "
"recitation."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs0.7"
msgid "Namo tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr "Homage to the Master, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.1.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa3"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena hatthako sakyaputto vādakkhitto hoti."
msgstr "At that time Hatthaka the Sakyan had been beaten in debate."

#. According to <ref>Sp.4.736.6</ref> this means: “Before the meal, etc., he would make an appointment, saying, ‘Let there be a debate at such-and-such a time and at such-and-such a place,’ and he would then go there before or after the time of the appointment, saying, ‘Look, sirs, the ascetics of other sects have not come; they are defeated,’ and he would then depart,” <i lang="pli">purebhattādīsu, “asukasmiṃ nāma kāle asukasmiṃ nāma padese vādo hotū”ti saṅketaṃ katvā saṅketato pure vā pacchā vā gantvā, “passatha bho, titthiyā na āgatā parājitā”ti pakkamati</i>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.3"
msgid ""
"So titthiyehi saddhiṃ sallapanto avajānitvā paṭijānāti, paṭijānitvā "
"avajānāti, aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, sampajānamusā bhāsati, saṅketaṃ katvā "
"visaṃvādeti."
msgstr ""
"While talking with ascetics of other sects, he would assert things after "
"denying them, and he would deny things after asserting them. He evaded the "
"issues, lied, and made sham appointments."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.165"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.4"
msgid ""
"Titthiyā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—“kathañhi nāma hatthako sakyaputto "
"amhehi saddhiṃ sallapanto avajānitvā paṭijānissati, paṭijānitvā "
"avajānissati, aññenaññaṃ paṭicarissati, sampajānamusā bhāsissati, saṅketaṃ "
"katvā visaṃvādessatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"The ascetics of other sects complained and criticized him, “When Hatthaka "
"talks with us, how can he assert things after denying them, deny things "
"after asserting them, evade the issues, lie, and make sham appointments?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa4"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.5"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ titthiyānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ "
"vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those ascetics of other sects,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū yena hatthako sakyaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"hatthakaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and they went to Hatthaka and said, "

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.7"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, āvuso hatthaka, titthiyehi saddhiṃ sallapanto avajānitvā "
"paṭijānāsi, paṭijānitvā avajānāsi, aññenaññaṃ paṭicarasi, sampajānamusā "
"bhāsasi, saṅketaṃ katvā visaṃvādesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Hatthaka, that you are acting like this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "“Ete kho, āvuso, titthiyā nāma yena kenaci jetabbā;"
msgstr "“These ascetics of other sects should be beaten, whatever it takes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "neva tesaṃ jayo dātabbo”ti."
msgstr "They should not be allowed to win.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe … te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The monks of few desires … complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.11"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma hatthako sakyaputto titthiyehi saddhiṃ sallapanto avajānitvā "
"paṭijānissati, paṭijānitvā avajānissati, aññenaññaṃ paṭicarissati, "
"sampajānamusā bhāsissati, saṅketaṃ katvā visaṃvādessatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“When Hatthaka talks with ascetics of other sects, how can he assert things "
"after denying them, deny things after asserting them, evade the issues, lie, "
"and make sham appointments?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa5"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.12"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū hatthakaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "After criticizing Hatthaka in many ways, they told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.13"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ "
"sannipātāpetvā hatthakaṃ sakyaputtaṃ paṭipucchi—"
msgstr ""
"The Master then had the Order of monks assembled and questioned Hatthaka,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.14"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, hatthaka, titthiyehi saddhiṃ sallapanto avajānitvā "
"paṭijānāsi, paṭijānitvā avajānāsi, aññenaññaṃ paṭicarasi, sampajānamusā "
"bhāsasi, saṅketaṃ katvā visaṃvādesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Hatthaka, that you are acting like this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, "

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.17"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, titthiyehi saddhiṃ sallapanto avajānitvā "
"paṭijānissasi, paṭijānitvā avajānissasi, aññenaññaṃ paṭicarissasi, "
"sampajānamusā bhāsissasi, saṅketaṃ katvā visaṃvādessasi."
msgstr ""
"“… Foolish man, when you talk with ascetics of other sects, how can you "
"assert things after denying them, deny things after asserting them, evade "
"the issues, lie, and make sham appointments?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.19a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.166"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa6"></a><a class="sc" id="6"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "“Sampajānamusāvāde pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk lies in full awareness, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs1.21"
msgid "(<em>1</em>:<strong>50</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.1.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.1.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa7"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Sampajānamusāvādo nāma"
msgstr "Lies in full awareness:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.167"></a>
#. Although <i lang="pli">muta</i> normally means “thought,” translating as “sensed” is necessary in light of the next paragraph.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid ""
"visaṃvādanapurekkhārassa vācā, girā, byappatho, vacībhedo, vācasikā "
"viññatti, aṭṭha anariyavohārā—adiṭṭhaṃ diṭṭhaṃ meti, assutaṃ sutaṃ meti, "
"amutaṃ mutaṃ meti, aviññātaṃ viññātaṃ meti, diṭṭhaṃ adiṭṭhaṃ meti, sutaṃ "
"assutaṃ meti, mutaṃ amutaṃ meti, viññātaṃ aviññātaṃ meti."
msgstr ""
"the speech of one who is intent on deceiving—his words, his way of speaking, "
"his breaking into speech, his verbal expression, his eight kinds of ignoble "
"speech: he says that he has seen what he has not seen; he says that he has "
"heard what he has not heard; he says that he has sensed what he has not "
"sensed; he says that he has known what he has not known; he says that he has "
"not seen what he has seen; he says that he has not heard what he has heard; "
"he says that he has not sensed what he has sensed; he says that he has not "
"known what he has known."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.2a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.2b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa8"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "Adiṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Not seen:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "na cakkhunā diṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "not seen with the eye."

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "Assutaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Not heard:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "na sotena sutaṃ."
msgstr "not heard with the ear."

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "Amutaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Not sensed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "na ghānena ghāyitaṃ, na jivhāya sāyitaṃ, na kāyena phuṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"not smelled with the nose, not tasted with the tongue, not touched with the "
"body."

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "Aviññātaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Not known:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "na manasā viññātaṃ."
msgstr "not known with the mind."

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "Diṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Seen:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "cakkhunā diṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "seen with the eye."

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "Sutaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Heard:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "sotena sutaṃ."
msgstr "heard with the ear."

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "Mutaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Sensed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "ghānena ghāyitaṃ, jivhāya sāyitaṃ, kāyena phuṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "smelled with the nose, tasted with the tongue, touched with the body."

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "Viññātaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Known:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "manasā viññātaṃ."
msgstr "known with the mind."

#. </span></p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Exposition"

#. </h4><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr ""
"Falsely claiming to have experienced what he has not experienced: a single "
"sense door"

#. </h5><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.1.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa9"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid ""
"Tīhākārehi “adiṭṭhaṃ diṭṭhaṃ me”ti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti "
"pācittiyassa—"
msgstr ""
"If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen what he has not seen, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are "
"fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid ""
"pubbevassa hoti “musā bhaṇissan”ti, bhaṇantassa hoti “musā bhaṇāmī”ti, "
"bhaṇitassa hoti “musā mayā bhaṇitan”ti."
msgstr ""
"before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie; while lying, he knows he is "
"lying; after he has lied, he knows he has lied."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa10"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Catūhākārehi “adiṭṭhaṃ diṭṭhaṃ me”ti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti "
"pācittiyassa—"
msgstr ""
"If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen what he has not seen, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession when four conditions are "
"fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid ""
"pubbevassa hoti “musā bhaṇissan”ti, bhaṇantassa hoti “musā bhaṇāmī”ti, "
"bhaṇitassa hoti “musā mayā bhaṇitan”ti, vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ."
msgstr ""
"before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie; while lying, he knows he is "
"lying; after he has lied, he knows he has lied; in misrepresenting his view "
"of what is true."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa11"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid ""
"Pañcahākārehi “adiṭṭhaṃ diṭṭhaṃ me”ti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti "
"pācittiyassa—"
msgstr ""
"If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen what he has not seen, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession when five conditions are "
"fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid ""
"pubbevassa hoti “musā bhaṇissan”ti, bhaṇantassa hoti “musā bhaṇāmī”ti, "
"bhaṇitassa hoti “musā mayā bhaṇitan”ti, vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ, vinidhāya khantiṃ."
msgstr ""
"before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie; while lying, he knows he is "
"lying; after he has lied, he knows he has lied; in misrepresenting his view "
"of what is true; in misrepresenting his belief of what is true."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa12"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid ""
"Chahākārehi “adiṭṭhaṃ diṭṭhaṃ me”ti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti "
"pācittiyassa—"
msgstr ""
"If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen what he has not seen, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession when six conditions are fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid ""
"pubbevassa hoti “musā bhaṇissan”ti, bhaṇantassa hoti “musā bhaṇāmī”ti, "
"bhaṇitassa hoti “musā mayā bhaṇitan”ti, vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ, vinidhāya "
"khantiṃ, vinidhāya ruciṃ."
msgstr ""
"before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie; while lying, he knows he is "
"lying; after he has lied, he knows he has lied; in misrepresenting his view "
"of what is true; in misrepresenting his belief of what is true; in "
"misrepresenting his acceptance of what is true."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa13"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.9"
msgid ""
"Sattahākārehi “adiṭṭhaṃ diṭṭhaṃ me”ti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti "
"pācittiyassa—"
msgstr ""
"If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen what he has not seen, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession when seven conditions are "
"fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.10"
msgid ""
"pubbevassa hoti “musā bhaṇissan”ti, bhaṇantassa hoti “musā bhaṇāmī”ti, "
"bhaṇitassa hoti “musā mayā bhaṇitan”ti, vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ, vinidhāya "
"khantiṃ, vinidhāya ruciṃ, vinidhāya bhāvaṃ."
msgstr ""
"before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie; while lying, he knows he is "
"lying; after he has lied, he knows he has lied; in misrepresenting his view "
"of what is true; in misrepresenting his belief of what is true; in "
"misrepresenting his acceptance of what is true; in misrepresenting his "
"sentiment of what is true."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa14"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.11"
msgid "Tīhākārehi “assutaṃ sutaṃ me”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"If he lies in full awareness, saying that he says that he has heard what he "
"has not heard …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.12"
msgid "amutaṃ mutaṃ meti … pe …"
msgstr "saying that he has sensed what he has not sensed …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.13"
msgid "aviññātaṃ viññātaṃ meti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa—"
msgstr ""
"saying that he has known what he has not known, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.2.14"
msgid ""
"pubbevassa hoti “musā bhaṇissan”ti, bhaṇantassa hoti “musā bhaṇāmī”ti, "
"bhaṇitassa hoti “musā mayā bhaṇitan”ti."
msgstr ""
"before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie; while lying, he knows he is "
"lying; after he has lied, he knows he has lied."

