msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.6.5"
msgid "viññātaṃ pamuṭṭho hoti … viññātañca me sutañcāti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"is confused about what he has known, but he lies in full awareness, saying "
"that he has known and heard …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.6.6"
msgid "viññātaṃ pamuṭṭho hoti; viññātañca me mutañcāti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"is confused about what he has known, but he lies in full awareness, saying "
"that he has known and sensed …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.6.7"
msgid "viññātaṃ pamuṭṭho hoti; viññātañca me diṭṭhañca sutañcāti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"is confused about what he has known, but he lies in full awareness, saying "
"that he has known and seen and heard …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.6.8"
msgid "viññātaṃ pamuṭṭho hoti; viññātañca me diṭṭhañca mutañcāti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"is confused about what he has known, but he lies in full awareness, saying "
"that he has known and seen and sensed …"

#. This series, too, seems to be missing one combination: “… saying that he has known and heard and sensed what he has seen …”.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.6.9"
msgid ""
"viññātaṃ pamuṭṭho hoti; viññātañca me diṭṭhañca sutañca mutañcāti "
"sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"is confused about what he has known, but he lies in full awareness, saying "
"that he has known and seen and heard and sensed, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa26"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.6.10"
msgid "Catūhākārehi … pe …"
msgstr "… when four conditions are fulfilled …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.6.11"
msgid "pañcahākārehi … pe …"
msgstr "when five conditions are fulfilled …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.6.12"
msgid "chahākārehi … pe …"
msgstr "when six conditions are fulfilled …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.6.13"
msgid ""
"sattahākārehi … pe … viññātaṃ pamuṭṭho hoti, viññātañca me diṭṭhañca sutañca "
"mutañcāti sampajānamusā bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa—"
msgstr ""
"is confused about what he has known, but he lies in full awareness, saying "
"that he has known and seen and heard and sensed, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession when seven conditions are fulfilled:"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.170"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.6.14"
msgid ""
"pubbevassa hoti “musā bhaṇissan”ti, bhaṇantassa hoti “musā bhaṇāmī”ti, "
"bhaṇitassa hoti “musā mayā bhaṇitan”ti, vinidhāya diṭṭhiṃ, vinidhāya "
"khantiṃ, vinidhāya ruciṃ, vinidhāya bhāvaṃ."
msgstr ""
"before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie; while lying, he knows he is "
"lying; after he has lied, he knows he has lied; in misrepresenting his view "
"of what is true; in misrepresenting his belief of what is true; in "
"misrepresenting his acceptance of what is true; in misrepresenting his "
"sentiment of what is true."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.7.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.1.2.7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa27"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.7.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

#. VAR: ravā bhaṇati → ravāya bhaṇati (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.7.2"
msgid "davā bhaṇati, ravā bhaṇati."
msgstr "if he speaks playfully; if he is speaks too fast;"

#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.7.3"
msgid "“Davā bhaṇati nāma"
msgstr "(speaks playfully means:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.7.4"
msgid "sahasā bhaṇati."
msgstr "speaking quickly; "

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.7.5"
msgid "Ravā bhaṇati nāma"
msgstr "speaks too fast means:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.7.6"
msgid "‘aññaṃ bhaṇissāmī’ti aññaṃ bhaṇati”."
msgstr "thinking to say one thing, he says something else);"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.7.7"
msgid "Ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.7.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa28"></a> 
#. VAR: Musāvādasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ → paṭha­ma­sikkhā­padaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc1:pts-cs2.7.9"
msgid "Musāvādasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The first rule, the training rule on lying, is finished."

